# Agent Pipeline Protocol

## Architecture

The pipeline runs in the Cursor chat (you), and the visual overlay runs in the browser (`npm run dev`). The bridge between them is a single JSON file:

```
cursor/agents/pipeline-status.json
```

The overlay polls this file every 3 seconds. When you update it, the overlay updates automatically.

## Who Controls the File

**Zeus (the Master Agent) is the ONLY entity that writes to pipeline-status.json.** Individual agents do NOT write to this file — Zeus handles all state transitions.

When the user sends the starter prompt, the chat agent assumes the role of Zeus and then sequentially assumes each sub-agent's role, updating pipeline-status.json at every transition.

## Pipeline Status File Format

```json
{
  "currentAgent": "hermes",
  "phase": "running",
  "queue": ["athena", "apollo", "artemis", "hephaestus", "poseidon", "hera", "hestia", "ares", "hades", "perseus"],
  "completed": {
    "hermes": {
      "startedAt": "2026-03-28T12:00:00.000Z",
      "completedAt": "2026-03-28T12:05:00.000Z",
      "elapsedMs": 300000,
      "summary": "Extracted requirements from briefing"
    }
  },
  "startedAt": "2026-03-28T12:00:00.000Z"
}
```

### Phase Values
- `"idle"` — pipeline not started
- `"running"` — pipeline in progress
- `"completed"` — all agents finished

### Parallel Agents
For parallel stages (Apollo+Artemis, Hades+Perseus), `currentAgent` can be an array:
```json
{ "currentAgent": ["apollo", "artemis"] }
```

## Individual Agent Output

Each agent also writes a `status.json` to their own `output/` folder:

```json
{
  "agent": "hermes",
  "status": "completed",
  "startedAt": "2026-03-28T12:00:00.000Z",
  "completedAt": "2026-03-28T12:05:00.000Z",
  "elapsedMs": 300000,
  "summary": "Brief description of what was done",
  "outputFiles": ["scope.md", "sitemap.md", "user-flows.md"]
}
```

